®In Loving Memory of
Chris and Beatrice Bailey Hughes of Crewe
Wonderful grandparents
who loved the Orme

IN LOVING MEMORY OF
Mr & Mrs J.A.Hedgecock
OF NOTTINGHAM"∞
≠LIFE LONG PARTNERS
LESLIE & MARY WOODWARD
OF GOGARTH ROAD LLANDUDNO
TOGETHER FOREVER
AFTER A LIFETIME OF HAPPINESS
AND TRUE LOVE

FRANK & ALMA LESTER REUNITED
WE HOLD YOU CLOSE WITHIN OUR HEARTS
THERE YOU WILL REMAIN
TO WALK WITH US THROUGHOUT OUR LIVES
UNTIL WE MEET AGAIN
NIGHT GOD BLESS"≤
ØIN LOVING MEMORY OF
KEITH BAILEY
FROM WIGAN, LANCS, WHO SADLY PASSED AWAY
WHILST HERE IN LLANDUDNO IN 2004
GREATLY MISSED BY ALL HIS LOVING FAMILY HE WAS,
SIMPLY THE BEST"≤
ØTreasured Memories of
MARJORIE (Bray)
of Meltham, Holmfirth
Who Died June 2004
She loved this place and the beautiful views from it.
Till we meet again-All my love-Arnold"≤
ØJoe Mountain (Halifax)
24/03/1932 - 18/06/2016
Your memory is a keepsake with which we'll never part
God has you in his keeping, we have you in our heart

IN LOVING MEMORY
OUR FAMILY CHAIN IS BROKEN
NOTHING FEELS THE SAME
BUT AS GOD CALLS US
ONE BY ONE
THE LINKS WILL
JOIN AGAIN
üñ§üñ§üñ§"…
∆Every day, in some small way,
memories of you come our way.
Though absent, you are ever near.
Still missed, still loved, and ever dear.
In Loving Memory of
Rick, Josie, Brian and Richard Powney"À
»IN LOVING MEMORY OF OUR WONDERFUL MUM
A LIFETIME OF LOVE AND DEVOTION
HOW PRIVILEGED WE WERE
FOR GUIDING US THROUGH THE YEARS WHEN WE WERE YOUNG
SHOWING US THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN RIGHT AND WRONG
LOVING US THOUGH SOMETIMES WE LET YOU DOWN
FOR FORGIVING US WHEN WE WERE NOWHERE TO BE FOUND
GOOD NIGHT AND GOD BLESS BEAUTIFUL ANGEL
WE MISS YOU SO VERY VERY MUCH
SUSAN, PETER, ALAN AND ROBERT

IN LOVING MEMORY oF
TWIZZLE
LESLEY JANE MABON
YOU'D ARRIVE WITH THE MORNING SUN
AND WITH THE MIDNIGHT TIDE YOU WOULD LEAVE
JUST WHEN I NEEDED YOU MORE THAN ANYONE
MORE THAN ANYONE EVER NEEDED ME
GOOD NIGHT AND GOD BLESS MY DARLING
